1932
J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York
Negative No. 237
The New York Sun of December 22, 1938 reports the filing of plans for a modern, 6 story apartment on the present site of Nos. 517-21 E. 86th Street. This structure, at a cost of ~175,000 will rise to the west of Misercorde Hospital and stand where the
three buildings in the larger view are.
